---
/**
 * /legend-maker — Landing page for the Legend-Maker Scroll.
 *
 * Routes:
 *   /legend-maker          → this page (pitch + email capture)
 *   /legend-maker/scroll   → the full scroll (next file)
 *
 * IMPORTANT: Replace the form action (#FORM_ACTION) with your email provider's
 * endpoint — ConvertKit, Mailchimp, Buttondown, Netlify Forms, etc. As shipped
 * it falls back to a Netlify Forms-compatible setup (data-netlify="true").
 */

import LegendMakerLayout from "../../layouts/LegendMakerLayout.astro";

const title = "The Legend-Maker Scroll — 701am";
const description =
  "The method we use in the office, written down. How to find the angle, write the pitch, and earn the placement. No fee. No funnel. Just the work.";
---

<LegendMakerLayout
  title={title}
  description={description}
  breadcrumbs={[
    { name: 'Home', url: '/' },
    { name: 'The Scroll' },
  ]}
>
  <!-- HERO -->
  <section class="lm-hero">
    <div class="lm-container">
      <div class="lm-hero__edition">
        <span>Vol. I — The Method</span>
        <span>701am.com / Legend-Maker</span>
      </div>

      <h1 class="lm-hero__title">
        The Legend-Maker <em>Scroll.</em>
      </h1>

      <p class="lm-hero__lede">
        How to build a data story the press cannot ignore.
      </p>

      <div class="lm-hero__byline">
        <div>
          <strong>From</strong>
          The desk at 701am
        </div>
        <div>
          <strong>For</strong>
          Founders, marketers, agency operators
        </div>
        <div>
          <strong>Length</strong>
          About 35 minutes
        </div>
        <div>
          <strong>Price</strong>
          Free. No funnel.
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- DEK / BLURB -->
  <section class="lm-dek">
    <div class="lm-container">
      <div class="lm-dek__grid">
        <div class="lm-dek__label">The Promise</div>
        <div class="lm-dek__body">
          <p>
            The same method we use in the office, written down, sent to your inbox.
            <strong>How to find the angle. How to write the pitch. How to earn the placement.</strong>
            No fee. No funnel. Just the work.
          </p>
          <p>
            This is the playbook for building a data story unique to your business — by
            combining <em>two public datasets nobody has thought to multiply</em> into a
            number that did not exist this morning. Editors approve those stories.
            Reporters chase them. Competitors cannot copy them.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- STATS / WHY THIS WORKS -->
  <section class="lm-container" style="padding-top: clamp(3rem, 6vw, 5rem); padding-bottom: 0;">
    <div class="lm-stat-row">
      <div class="lm-stat">
        <div class="lm-stat__num">2</div>
        <div class="lm-stat__label">
          Public datasets, multiplied. One number that did not exist before you calculated it.
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="lm-stat">
        <div class="lm-stat__num">7</div>
        <div class="lm-stat__label">
          Steps from blank page to a story sitting in a reporter's inbox. One week of work.
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="lm-stat">
        <div class="lm-stat__num">1</div>
        <div class="lm-stat__label">
          Method. The same one we run every week. Now yours to keep.
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- METHOD GRID -->
  <section class="lm-method">
    <div class="lm-container">
      <div class="lm-method__head">
        <span class="lm-eyebrow">What you'll learn</span>
        <h2>Six things most PR advice gets wrong — and the inversions that work.</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="lm-method__grid">
        <div class="lm-method__cell">
          <span class="lm-method__num">01 / The Theory</span>
          <h3>Why your product is not your angle.</h3>
          <p>
            Reporters cover beats, not companies. The job is to find a story on the
            reporter's beat that requires your data to be told.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="lm-method__cell">
          <span class="lm-method__num">02 / The Two-Dataset Rule</span>
          <h3>One dataset is journalism the press has already done.</h3>
          <p>
            But two boring public datasets, multiplied, make one interesting number
            that nobody can re-report without crediting you.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="lm-method__cell">
          <span class="lm-method__num">03 / The Headline Test</span>
          <h3>If you cannot write the headline, you do not have a story.</h3>
          <p>
            Headlines are the editor's pre-approval. Write yours before you write the
            pitch — and walk away if it won't come.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="lm-method__cell">
          <span class="lm-method__num">04 / The Press Kit</span>
          <h3>Three documents. Not thirty.</h3>
          <p>
            A one-page brief, a methodology document, and a clean dataset. Send those
            three. Skip the brand book.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="lm-method__cell">
          <span class="lm-method__num">05 / The Pitch</span>
          <h3>120 words, four lines, one finding.</h3>
          <p>
            The pitch is not a press release. It is a sentence designed to be forwarded.
            Templates included.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="lm-method__cell">
          <span class="lm-method__num">06 / The Follow-Up</span>
          <h3>One follow-up. Then move on.</h3>
          <p>
            Two emails is the etiquette. The third is what gets you blocked. The
            sequence, the tracker, and what to do after the placement.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- EMAIL CAPTURE -->
  <section class="lm-capture" id="capture">
    <div class="lm-container">
      <div class="lm-capture__inner">
        <div>
          <span class="lm-eyebrow">Get the Scroll</span>
          <h2 style="margin-top: 1rem;">
            Sent to your inbox. <em>Free.</em>
          </h2>
          <p class="lm-capture__copy">
            Drop your email. We send the full Legend-Maker Scroll — the seven-step
            playbook, the templates, the checklist. No drip. No upsell. One file.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!--
          FORM: As shipped this works with Netlify Forms out of the box.
          To use another provider (ConvertKit, Mailchimp, Buttondown):
            1. Change `action` to your provider's POST endpoint
            2. Remove `data-netlify` and the hidden `form-name` input
            3. Adjust field `name` attributes to match the provider's schema
        -->
        <form
          class="lm-form"
          name="legend-maker"
          method="POST"
          action="/legend-maker/thanks"
          data-netlify="true"
          netlify-honeypot="bot-field"
        >
          <input type="hidden" name="form-name" value="legend-maker" />
          <p hidden>
            <label>Don't fill: <input name="bot-field" /></label>
          </p>

          <label for="lm-email">Your work email</label>
          <input
            type="email"
            id="lm-email"
            name="email"
            required
            placeholder="you@company.com"
            autocomplete="email"
          />

          <button type="submit">Send me the Scroll →</button>

          <p class="lm-form__note">
            We send the file once. We don't sell, share, or drip. Unsubscribe with one click.
          </p>
        </form>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- BRIDGE TO THE FULL SCROLL -->
  <section style="padding: var(--section-pad) 0;">
    <div class="lm-container lm-container--narrow" style="text-align: center;">
      <span class="lm-eyebrow" style="justify-content: center;">Or read it now</span>
      <h2 style="font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 2.75rem); font-weight: 300; margin: 1.5rem 0 1.25rem; letter-spacing: -0.03em;">
        Don't want to wait for an email?
      </h2>
      <p style="font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: 1.15rem; font-style: italic; color: var(--ink-soft); max-width: 38ch; margin: 0 auto 2rem;">
        The full scroll lives at a permanent URL. Bookmark it, link it, send it to a colleague.
      </p>
      <a href="/legend-maker/scroll" class="lm-btn">Read the full Scroll →</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</LegendMakerLayout>
